properties.opinion: The kind of neighborhood coffee house that actually feels like it's part of a neighborhood. Community bulletin boards, bookshelves, sometimes local art. properties.name: Pie Me Café
properties.opinion:
Auch wenn es ein Café ist, sind wir hier Stammkunden zum warm Essen. Die australischen Pies haben eine große Auswahl und sind lecker. Ich empfehle sie im Menü zu kaufen, denn der Kartoffelbrei und der Salat sind aucm immer sehr gut. Die Desserts wie der Möhrenkuchen oder die Zimtrollen sind auch sehr zu empfehlen.

Die Getränke sind wie zu erwarten in einem hippen Café, viele Milchkaffees, Matcha-Latte etc, sehr solide und der Kaffee ist nicht schlecht. Persönlich mag ich eher handgebraute Spezialitätencafés, aber dafür ist das nicht der Ort, was auch okay ist.

properties.name: Kleiner Herd, Großes Feuer
properties.opinion: Kleines tibetisches Restaurant. Es bietet tibetische Maultaschen an und Nudelsuppen, beides nur in ein paar Varianten, die Auswahl ist also limitiert. Aber es ist alles Handgemacht, die Teigtaschen werden von Hand gefalten und die Nudeln sind auch selbst gemacht. Es scheint sehr authentisch und schmeckstauch sehr gut. Ist dafür etwas teurer als der Tibet-Imbiss in Poppelsdorf und man muss sich auch etwas gedulden bis das Essen fertig ist. Und der Innenbereich ist sehr klein, manchmal findet man nicht leicht einen Platz. Also ist es nichts, wo man mit großen Gruppen hinkommen sollte. Zum Mitnehmen sollte man selbst einen Behälter mitbringen.

properties.name: Hana Asia-Shop
properties.opinion:
It's the go-to store if you want authentic Korean food. The owner sells home-made Kimchi which is much better than the company-made Kimchi you find in other asian stores, and you also find great side-dishes. The owner is also very helpful ano will ask you immediately what you want, don't be intimmidated :). The prices for some products (e.g. tofu) are higher than in the big asia supermarkets but I understand that at as a small store it's hard to compete. Otherwise it's small, so if you want non-Korean asian products, they might be missing here, it's very small after all.

My review might be a bit biaseo because I had a lot of small-talk with the owner and we have gotten a bit friendly.

Pretty bad.  Dirty room with salsa on the rug and a corn nut and human hair and stickiness on various walls and furniture. I guess adults don't care about peace and quiet?  The restaurants are absolutely awful.  Super expensive for extremely mediocre food with a live smooth jazz "artist" blasting his saxophone in your face.  Constant expectations for tips for everything, including the bills which already have substantial service charges.  Charge $17/day for usable internet when you pay  $465/night.  The management was professional and removed the internet charge and gave us a discount for the night club noise - but it was like a fight for everything.  Wont be back.

properties.opinion: We knew this was a low-brow spot, but low-brow spots can be awesome - unfortunately, this was not, and we wont be back.  Awkward ordering system and mediocre food.  They have this thing with "salty vegetables", like greenbeans - but it was really hard to think into the culinary culture of what was being presented.  They were cooked well, just doused in a lot of salt.  Standard pork buns could have been much better.  I remember sort of liking dim-sum, but it's been a long time.  Just felt like lots of things were the same rigid shrimp paste, with slightly undercooked shrimp (and other things) inside.  But most of all, the feeling was you were sitting at a place where you did take-out with your phone.  No service beyond that.

properties.name: Hackerspace Brussels
properties.opinion:
We were looking for a space to organize our Openstreetmap mapathon and HSBXL was very open to letting us use their space. I must say Wouter, who was overseeing the space at the time, was VERY welcoming. Noticed I was wearing a mask (no requirement at the time of writing this) and immediately asked if he should open a window for me (to get some fresh air).

The space itself is (at the time of writing) located in a pretty cool and unique location, an old office building. It definitely fits with the hackerspace feel. At first it seems hard to find but when you enter the courtyard it's located at, you immediately realize you're at the right place. As with most hackerspaces, I assume(?), the fridge/snackstorage works with a trust system where you just deposit the money of whatever you take. (you can pay with cash, bankcard, bank transfer).

It's a shame this location might disappear by the end of the year, but i'm sure they'll find something with a similar vibe!

Og Når man har gået tur med hunden kan man spise eller få en drink på Hotel Fortunen, hvor man også kan parkere.

properties.name: Kafe Kapers
properties.opinion:
Hyggelig cafe på Østerfælled torv i et firkantet glashus.
Hunde er velkomne i pavillion-afdelingen.

properties.name: Geelskov
properties.opinion: Ikke indhegnet. Men stort område med masser af skov, skrænter og høje, hvor en hund virkelig kan more sig med at udforske det hele.

properties.name: Bernstorffsparken
properties.opinion: Meget populært sted at tage hunden. Parken er indhegnet bortset fra ved et par af indgangene.

properties.name: Oxbjerget Hundefold
properties.opinion: Dejligt område med en stor bakke. Det er tæt på motorvjen og der en lille kiosk.

properties.name: Trianglen Store Hundegård
properties.opinion: Den større hundegård i fælledparken. Der er som regel lidt større hunde end i den lille hundegård. Der er ikke megen bevoksning. Men der nogle træer og der et ret kuperet tærren. Der er vand til hunden og et fint picnic bord.

properties.name: Fælledparken løbegård
properties.opinion:
Den mindste af de to løbegårde i fælledparken. Der er ikke rigtigt nogen græs tilbage. Det er mest jord og grus og nogle træer. Men det er jo sådan det må være for en af de få hundeparker i København.
Normalt er her lidt mindre hunde end i den store hundegård.

properties.name: Hedeland Nord Hundeskov
properties.opinion: It has a long narrow piece along the train track and a bigger open area at the end.

properties.name: Staurby Skov hundeskov
properties.opinion: Meget fin og vedligeholdt hundeskov med hvalpegård, helt nyt overdækket borde/bænke. Dejlig afvekslende med flere typer skov og åbne områder. Og så er det meget nemt at komme til og fra motorvejen, så det er helt perfekt hvis man er på en længere tur og hunden har brug for at få rørt poterne.
